		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+16" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">Dear Jonathon,</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="_sans" SIZE="12" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"> </FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">Sorry I haven't been in touch for a while but I've been rather busy job hunting! Yes, I'm afraid I lost my fabulous job! I'm sure you remember how I boasted about the wonderful working conditions - the <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[1]</FONT> that meant I could work when I wanted to, and the wonderful <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[2]</FONT> of promotion! Well, I was made <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[3]</FONT> in March. I should have seen it coming really. The economic <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[4]</FONT> here led to a dramatic drop in sales, which affected the company's <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[5]</FONT> so badly that it almost went <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[6]</FONT> at the end of last year. </FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="_sans" SIZE="12" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"> </FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">Then in February things started to look up as another company in the same field stepped in and a <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[7]</FONT> took place. When that happened, I thought I might just keep my job, but they decided that they didn't need such a big <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[8]</FONT>, and one of the first things they did was to <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[9]</FONT> the company and <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[10]</FONT> a lot of the work to consultants and other companies.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="_sans" SIZE="12" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"> </FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">Anyway, since then I've been to at least twenty interviews but I'm getting nowhere. It's quite depressing actually because I've spent years getting the perfect <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[11]</FONT> together and it's looking really good now. I've got over fifteen years' experience in the marketing field, I've been on lots of courses and I've picked up quite a few <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[12]</FONT> along the way. I've also got some great <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[13]</FONT> from previous employers but it seems that the <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[14]</FONT> is just flooded with people like me. </FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="_sans" SIZE="12" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"> </FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">What's more nobody wants to take on new staff in the present economic climate, at least not on full-time contracts. One company asked me if I was interested in <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[15]</FONT> - can you imagine that? Half the pay for probably just as much work! I'm seriously considering <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[16]</FONT> - I've got my own computer and an Internet connection and I quite fancy the idea of working from home for a change.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="_sans" SIZE="12" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0"> </FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
